cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.DL, cs.DB, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with the compression of ranked ordered trees, which is a fundamental data structure in computer science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also introduces a new algorithm and compares it with similar compression algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DL (Digital Libraries). The use of linear straight-line context-free tree grammars and succinct coding also suggests that it could belong to cs.DB (Databases) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
